name: Automata
description: Artist David Brooks is a fan of Japanese artist Isao Tomita and his unique synthesized music. It's no surprise therefore that David took inspiration from Tomita's album covers when he painted Automata. For those unfamiliar with his work, Tomita is considered by many to be the grandfather of electronic music and space-music. Broadly, Automata refers to machines making tasks easier, more efficient and less mistake-prone and ultimately helping humans toward an easier if not brighter future. In David's representation, horizontal bands overlay the image of what could be a face. A stark canvas texture and an alluring vignette create a puzzling and mysterious image. This gorgeous abstract would compliment any well lit room.

name: Authentic Self
description: When he painted Authentic Self, artist David Brooks was pondering the question of how much of our true selves we reveal on our journeys through life.

name: Kaiseizan Park
description: David Brooks uses soft colours and experimental application of paint showing a freer style in his work. Kaiseizan Park is inspired by the cherry blossoms in the park of the same name near to his old home in Japan.

name: Sunshine Recorder
description: Another later artwork, Sunshine Recorder is a bold and evocative painting by artist, David Brooks. This textured, colourful piece would bring warmth and joy to any room.

name: SRB SEP
description: A painting for space enthusiasts, SRB SEP is David Brooksâ€™ evocation of NASAâ€™s space shuttle Solid Rocket Booster Separation. This striking artwork would make a great talking point in any home or workspace.

name: WFH 2.0
description: Working from home has become the new normal. Artist David Brooks pays homage to this new working world in his latest vibrant, exciting abstract WFH 2.0

name: The Coral Sea
description: A later work by artist David Brooks, The Coral Sea evokes romantic notions of pirate ships on tropical seas.

name: Fracture
description: Artist David Brooks imagined himself on an alien planet for his starting point for this painting. The beautiful blues of Fracture would lift any workspace or living room.

name: Flotilla
description: Inspired by his time in the Navy and by his love of the paintings of John Turner, artist David Brooks bring both together in this beautiful depiction of a flotilla of tall ships.

name: Physics Textbook Triptych
description: This triptych is artist David Brooks' abstract representation of diagrams of interaction of centrifugal forces and gravity. Having this contemporary art on your wall will be sure to make anyone gravitate towards it.

name: Pathumthani
description: A central province of Thailand gives its name to this painting. Pathumthani represents artist David Brooksâ€™ memories of his long journeys home to his family.

name: Aorpreeya
description: Artist David Brooks used his wifeâ€™s face as a starting point for this striking work of art. Aorpreeya would make a great talking point in any office or home.

name: Prospect
description: Artist David Brooks was inspired by pictures of the surface of Mars when he painted Prospect. The glowing shades of orange would bring warmth to the coolest office or den.

name: Transit
description: Artist David Brooks was imagining navigating through the far reaches of space when he painted Transit. Turquoise, azure and white are eye-catching in this piece thatâ€™s sure to brighten any room.

name: Will I Dream?
description: Homage to Kubrickâ€™s, 2001 A Space Odyssey, this representation of discovery would add some futuristic flair to any office.

name: Water House
description: In Water House (Ban Na) artist David Brooks depicts a Thai bamboo house next to a river. The house is lit faintly by the night sky.

name: Walk the Woods
description: Inspired by his memories of Canadian forests, Walk the Woods is artist David Brooks' journey into the forest. David brings the forest to life with yellow ochre, acid green, charcoal and crimson red.

name: The Kill
description: Stark monochrome and blood red evokes the savagery of the hunt in this jarring piece by artist, David Brooks.

name: The Horn
description: Do you see the faintest whisper of a break in the weather? The artist depicts a 19th century sailing ship battling the a notorious Cape Horn tempest in this atmospheric monochromic piece.

name: The City
description: A striking expression of urban sprawl, artist David Brooks uses reds, oranges and flame yellows to evoke the heat and bustle of an East Asian city. This bold, abstract painting would electrify any home or workspace.

name: Cassowary
description: In Cassowary, artist David Brooks uses reds, blues, yellows and greys in this emotionally-charged, abstract composition. This painting would make a great talking point in any home or workspace.

name: Storm Triptych
description: In Storm Triptych, artist David Brooks has brought to life the stages of a storm-ravaged tree. He depicts a torrent of emotions in warm orange, yellow, blue and in teal green and rich, earthy red.

name: Wall Garden
description: Through the clouds of confusion flower honey-dripping sparks of life. The fresh, green of fledgling new life, tulip scarlet and molten gold of Wall Garden brings warmth and vitality to this composition.

name: Tokyo Nights Pentaptych
description: David Brooks was remembering nights out in Roppongi, the clubbing district of Tokyo, when he painted this vivid red pentaptych. Bring the night life home with Tokyo Nights on your wall.

name: Reconnaisance
description: Artist David Brooks was inspired by aerial views of Mars when he painted Reconnaissance. The resulting effect is truly an out of this world experience.

name: Mekong Delta
description: Explore the tropical mangroves of the Mekong Delta. Sit in quiet contemplation. Greens, yellows, browns, reds, the faintest wisp of teal and the grey light of a tributary of this mighty south east Asian river.

name: Junk
description: In this vibrant painting artist David Brooks, Junk depicts a Chinese junk jockeying for position in an Asian fishing port at sunset. Feel mesmerised by the vivid shimmers of the neon lights on the water.

name: Kejimkujik

name: Dissolved Girl
description: Magenta, crimson, ultramarine, cyan, violet, yellowâ€¦ Dissolved Girl by artist David Brooks, is a rainbow face fading away in mists of colourâ€¦ Lose yourself in those eyes.

name: Clear Visibility

name: Chernobyl

name: Bamboo Hut
description: Artist David Brooks used muted yellow, soft greens and faintest crimson red to bring character and warmth to this painting. Bamboo Hut evokes life in the South East Asian rice paddies.

name: Autumn

name: Anathema

name: White Peonies
description: A recent abstract by artist Jim Ulrich, White Peonies is a depiction of the flowers in his wifeâ€™s garden.

name: Pathway

name: Illusion

name: Virus

name: The Storm

name: Wondered

name: Untitled

name: Surface No.2

name: Surface No.1
description: Molten copper and bronze bubble in this emotionally charged, all-over composition, Surface #1. Let yourself go with the flowâ€¦ Surface #1 is the fist in a series of three paintings by Canadian artist Jim Ulrich.

name: See Through

name: Midwinter Thailand No.5

description: In Flow Over, artist Jim Ulrich has created swirling patterns in raw sienna cut with bold violet, ultramarine and scarlet. This striking artwork depicts an aerial view of a landscape cut with running waterways.

name: Fall Sunset
description: October, the forest leaves are changing from green to yellow and orange. The weather is perfect. Go for a drive in the mountains to see the beautiful view of Fall Sunset.

name: Rudra Surya
description: The Rudras are a series of four paintings by Norman Sjoman. They started out as pathway icons like a hand on a rock wall indicating individual  presence and reminding us of what lasts. Rudra is the old god, the master of the uncreate who brought about creation.  In the same way the paintings present the individual in a less defined field.  Norman was exploring these ideas and realized he was doing it visually as well when he started on these paintings. These paintings were created in metallic, pearlescent paints and change colour in different light.

name: Bhuvanakrtimandalam
description: The final resolution in the Norman Sjoman's series of mandalas, Bhuvanakrtimandalam depicts the universe and the emptiness within. The caption in the void reads: 'The world of Siva (Rudra) is a mandala in the form of the universe. It's inside of you. It's your own body and it is identical with your own consciousness.' The painting comes from a circular meeting of shamans. The text is from an Atharva Veda hymn to a vanished divinity, Skambha.

name: Magic Hour

name: Symphony of Nature
description: Inspired by the autumn colours of a Canadian fall, Symphony of Nature by Jegan G Raja, would bring warmth to any space.

name: My Dream Home
description: Inspired by riversides in the Canadian wilderness, My Dream Home is a beautiful composition by Jegan G Raja. This painting would bring warmth and joy to any room.

name: Caribbean Sunset
description: A beautiful painting by Jegan Raja, Caribbean Sunset is inspired by the spectacular evening skies on the island of Cuba.

name: A Walk in the Woods
description: Imagine how romantic it would be to go for a walk in the woods with your lover... A Walk in the Woods by Jegan G Raja evokes the romance of true love.

name: Once Upon a Time
description: A once bustling and now abandoned barn in Ottawa was the inspiration for this painting by Jegan G Raja. This artwork evokes feelings of nostalgia for a time gone by.

name: Magical Sunset
description: Inspired by the colourful sky over Havana, Cuba, Magical Sunset is a stunning painting by Jegan G Raja. Jegan tells us that the sky speaks a thousand colours, reminding us that every sunset is an opportunity to reset our life.

name: Golden Hour
description: The sun is setting and the birds are home. This is the golden hour of the day. Reds and oranges bring warmth to this simple yet beautiful painting by Jegan G Raja.

name: Fall in Love
description: Artist Jegan G Raja was inspired by the infinitely beautiful colours of autumn in Ottawa when he painted Fall in Love. He observed that it is nature painting for us, day after day.

description: Using dark colours, artist Ed Bader takes a minimalist, geometric approach in his homage to American abstract expressionist Ad Reinhardt.

name: Tangerine Tango
description: Artist Ed Bader uses bold and expressive use of colour to create a distinct juxtaposition between the layers. A calculated use of balance and composition leads the viewer into a world of complimentary hues and vibrancy.

name: Mellow Yellow
description: Another bold and expressive use of colour, Mellow Yellow is Edward Bader's homage to The Beatles.

name: Pink Dawn Polka
description: Artist Ed Bader uses bold  and expressive use of colour to create a distinct juxtaposition between the light and the dark, or night and dawn. A calculated use of balance and composition leads the viewer into a world of complimentary hues and vibrancy.

name: Adagio for Agnes Martin
description: Artist Edward Bader uses pale, pastel shades to evoke calm in this homage to the art of Canadian abstract expressionist Agnes Martin.

name: Moon, Pines, Wall & Graffiti
description: Artist Edward Bader uses collage and a minimal style to create this simple composition.

name: Summertime
description: Artist Edward Bader took inspiration from the colour banners at festivals when he created this collage artwork.

name: Dancer
description: An abstract collage by Edward Bader, Dancer is inspired by figures in movement.

name: Homage to Turner
description: One of artist Edward Bader's inspirations is British artist John Turner - the painter of light. You can see his influence in this artwork.

name: Homage to Ernst
description: One of Edward Bader's inspirations is German artist Max Ernst - a pioneer of Dadaism and Surrealism. Homage to Ernst pays tribute.

name: Sunset for Paul
description: Edward Bader painted this for his friend, Paul, who would send him beautiful photos of Vancouver Island.

name: Blue Dawn
description: An expressionist abstract by Edward Bader, Blue Dawn evokes those serene few moments before the break of a new day.

name: What Would Happen
description: This piece is the first of a series where artist Rachel Cadrin began experimenting with painting in pairs. While painting What Would Happen, Rachel painted another work that mirrors the colours and feel of this painting. However, the space created is uniquely its own.

name: Oil Painting 5
description: The fifth painting in a series of seven paintings by Rachel Cadrin, Oil Painting 5 focused on creating depth of field through the exploration of colour. This is a mixed media piece and is canvas stretched over panel board. Due to the materials used this piece, it has a beautiful and interesting texture that draws the observer in.

name: Oil Painting 4
description: From a series in which artist Rachel Cadrin was using music as inspiration. Rachel created Oil Painting 4 listening to a specific song on repeat and allowing the cadence and tempo of the music to dictate her approach. Music impacted the overall mood of each piece in the series.

name: In the Midnight Hour
description: From a series in which artist Rachel Cadrin was using music as inspiration, Rachel created In the Midnight Hour while listening to a specific song and allowing the cadence and tempo of the music to dictate her approach. Music impacted the overall mood of each piece in the series and each one is named from a line in the song that was played during its creation.

name: Templo Mayor, 12 de octubre de 2018
description: Artist David Cheney was inspired to create Templo Mayor, 12 de Octubre de 2018 after his visit to Templo Mayor in Mexico City. The great temple and museum of the Mexica people is located right behind the cathedral and zocalo (main square).

name: Sixteenth Century Andalusian Love Sonnets and Other Rubbish

name: Looking for Dulcinea of Toboso by the Knight of the Sad Figure
description: Artist David Cheney was inspired by the happy meeting of sweethearts in Don Quijote de la Mancha when he created this artwork: Looking for Dulcinea of Toboso by the Knight of the Sad Figure.

name: Buscando las muralistas, JosÃ© Clemente Orozco
description: Artist David Cheney was inspired by the Mexican muralistas on a trip to Mexico City. As a result, he created Buscando Las Muralistas, Jose Clemente Orozco.

name: Albertine Disparue
description: Artist David Cheney was inspired by Marcel Proust's masterpiece, A la RecherchÃ© du Temps Perdu (In Search of Lost Time) when he created his homage to the sixth volume, Albertine Disparue.

name: Fun Money Currents (Up Flow)
description: One in a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. Fun Money Currents (Up Flow), "currents, the rhythmic movement of money, exchanges of goods and experiences. New growth is buoyed upward by the currents, reaching toward sunlight." This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic on canvas.

name: Fun Money Currents (Peacock)
description: One in a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. In Fun Money Currents, we are "hypnotized by the shiny prettiness of currency as it moves in patterns, bringing and taking away a continual flow of experiences through our lives." This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic on canvas.

name: Fun Money Wiggle 2
description: One of a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. In Fun Money Wiggle 2, "chocolate or bubblegum, did you get what you wanted out of your fun money?" This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic paint on canvas.

name: Fun Money Can I Lick It (Guilty Pleasures)
description: One of a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. In Can I Lick It (Guilty Pleasures) it's "breaking away from the soothing, repetitive and decorative surface enjoyment of money, it's time to get messy, peel back layers and transgress lifetime taboos of talking about money." This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic on canvas.

name: Fun Money Can I Lick It (Your Hidden Charms)
description: One of a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. In Can I Lick It (Your Hidden Charms) it's "thinking about the sensual experience of consuming these fun money coins, literally and metaphorically, having permission to use them up rather than conserving them, stockpiling them. Are they really used, or are they transformed?" This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic on canvas.

name: Fun Money Currents (Decorative)
description: One in a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. In Fun Money Currents, we are "hypnotized by the shiny prettiness of currency as it moves in patterns, bringing and taking away a continual flow of experiences through our lives." This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic on canvas.

name: Fun Money Currents (Downward Flow)
description: One in a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. Fun Money Currents (Downward Flow), "currents, the rhythmic movement of money, exchanges of goods and experiences. Outside influences, events from beyond, are dispersed and redirected by the flow of currency." This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic on canvas.

name: Fun Money Wiggle 1
description: One of a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. In Fun Money Wiggle 1, "chocolate or bubblegum, did you get what you wanted out of your fun money?" This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic paint on canvas.

name: Fun Money Pop
description: One of a series entitled Fun Money, artist Debbie.lee Miszaniec takes a playful look at her relationship with money. In Fun Money Pop, "round and round go the coins until we stop to look inside." This mixed-media creation uses foil and acrylic paint on canvas.

name: I Saw It Coming But It Was Too Late
description: Following on from his project with film-maker Anna Cooley in which he created paintings inspired by his meditations on the journey of the Covid-19 pandemic, Jim Ulrich now exhibits this more recent work, I Saw It Coming But It Was Too Late. This bold painting reflects his thoughts on the more recent Covid variants and our fears that this erratic and unpredictable virus may be far from over. This eye-catching abstract is sure to create a visual talking point in any home or workspace.

name: Full Moon Night Sky No.2
description: Artist Jim Ulrich was inspired by the evening view from his art studio in Beiseker, Alberta. This is one of two paintings in which he uses shades of blue to depict the effect of the full moon in brightening the night sky.

name: Full Moon Night Sky No.1
description: Artist Jim Ulrich was inspired by the evening view from his art studio in Beiseker, Alberta. This is one of two paintings in which he uses shades of blue to depict the effect of the full moon in brightening the night sky.

name: Aquarium
description: Artist Jim Ulrich took his inspiration from the fish tanks at the zoological aquarium in Ban Chang, Thailand, when he painted this recent piece.  With its vivid neon blues and splashes of red, Aquarium is a striking wall art that would bring to life to any living space.

name: Yellow Water
description: Artist Jim Ulrich spent time in Australia and Yellow Water is one of his paintings that draw on his memories of his travels there. He describes this piece as 'the morning light on a Northern Australian waterway filled with saltwater crocodiles - the calm before the storm'. A lovely painting, Yellow Water evokes a feeling of mindfulness and calm - the perfect addition to your 'work from home' space.

name: Stradbroke
description: Named for the island off the coast of Brisbane, Australia, Stradbroke is a new artwork by artist Jim Ulrich. Jim wanted to convey the juxtaposition of its aboriginal and colonial history and its beauty as a tropical paradise. With the start contrast of blue, red, yellow and white, Stradbroke's originality would make a great feature in any room.

name: Not Everything Has To Be About Something
description: In one of his more recent works, Not Everything Has To Be About Something, Jim Ulrich draws on his experience of the extreme weather both in western Canada and worldwide. Here he is questioning the apparent chaos of the global responses to the questions of global warming. This visually chaotic composition with its primary colors and swirling lines is Jim's abstract take on the chaos we all face as the crisis deepens beyond our control.

name: More Extreme Storms Will Bring...
description: In one of his more recent works, More Extreme Storms Will Bring..., Jim Ulrich draws on his experience of the climate crisis. Specifically the effects of global warming which has brought extreme weather both in western Canada and worldwide. This visually chaotic composition with its primary colors, pastel shades, and swirling lines is Jim's abstract take on the chaos we all face as the crisis deepens beyond our control.

description: This oil pastel on paper drawing is also part of the water series I've worked on over the years.

name: Waterform I
description: This oil pastel on paper drawing was inspired by the surface of ponds, where I wanted to capture the energy and potential of so much life in a pool of water.

name: Jumping Meadow
description: This oil pastel on paper drawing reminds me of the boundless energy of growth in the spring. This makes me happy and fills me with energy

name: First Snow
description: I grew up on the prairies and this reminds me of the fury in which autumn can turn to winter with one snowfall.

name: Detour
description: Influenced by the water series, this painting embodies the joy of freely moving paint across the surface of the canvas without expectations.

name: Spanish Splash
description: Another part of the waterfall series. I really enjoyed doing these paintings that were water influenced.

name: Slip Stream
description: Part of a series of paintings done after a boating accident and I went over a waterfall

name: Morning Sun
description: We live on the Yucatan Peninsula in Mexico our house faces North to Texas. The morning sun comes from the right as in this painting. Like most of these Acrylic on Yupo paper studies this was done for an audience on live video.

name: Dark Designs
description: This is a painting that I like more, the more I see it. Dark Designs was painted just before Virus for Sale. You can see I was having an interesting day. I did not like this at first. I forget what colors were squirted on the Yupo paper at the beginning, but they soon got all mixed up and became gray. I was using a homemade silicon tool to scrape through - my parallel linemaker. I look at it now and I see a thwarted struggle. Grey somewhat parallel lines pushing though, and continuing. Sometimes life feels like that.

name: Virus for Sale
description: I would say about this that my online viewers got to see anger and frustration in action with the mark making. One viewer, my husband, said it looks like a virus and the name stuck. I had been a little frustrated because my previous attempt on the paper had to be rinsed away. When I look at it now it looks evil.

name: Overlapping Thoughts
description: This was executed very quickly. Red and yellow squirted on and played with. Approaching 75, I wonder how anyone can control or organize all the random thoughts that flit through the mind hour after hour. I had no trouble naming this when I saw it the next morning. It seems to me anxious and frightening. As I look at it now I see drops of blood. I think I need to meditate more. This has been set to music on youtube and it is less scary.

name: Orange Regrets
description: A quick study using a new tool with yellow and red squirted on the yupo paper. This is a warm-up for me. I don't know why I named this Orange Regrets but that is the name that popped into my mind when I looked at it the next morning. All the happiness and alignment below and the stronger disruptions on the top may have made me think this. Right now - maybe I just made it up.

name: Blue Bridge
description: This was made during a demonstration of new art tools and was a response to the enjoying the new tool and the squirts of paint that had been added to the canvas. I usually name the piece the next day when I can see it with fresh eyes. 'Blue Bridge ' is a move from blue to now. If you see the video taken while I was doing it you will see that it is done very quickly - less than 2 minutes even when not speeded up. This is a warm-up study that I usually do before starting to work on larger piece. It is available for viewing on youtube and several other places online.
